    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-10T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-10T23:00:00-05:00" n="863"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d863">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 E.W./8–1044: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-11T00:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 11, 1944—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6370. For Ambassador and Herbert Pell. Proposed press statement transmitted in
                    despatch 17295, August 5 only just received and will promptly be submitted to
                    the consideration of the appropriate authorities.</p>
                <p>For Pell. Your telegram 6429, August 10. Request Sir Cecil Hurst to suspend
                    publicity until this Government has had opportunity to indicate its views
                    regarding statement which it will do at earliest possible moment.</p>
                <p>For Ambassador. If necessary, obtain Mr. Eden’s assistance to postpone
                        publicity.<note n="78" xml:id="d863fn78">Telegram 6627, August 17, from the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom reported that the press conference would be
                        called in about 10 days (740.00116 European War/8–1744).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
